  "notes": [
    "Pinned OCI SDK contract: CreateKnowledgeBase, GetKnowledgeBase, ListKnowledgeBases, ChangeKnowledgeBaseCompartment, UpdateKnowledgeBase, DeleteKnowledgeBase, and GetWorkRequest are present in v65.110.0. ListKnowledgeBases filters id, compartmentId, displayName, and lifecycleState, while the CRUD mutation responses expose opc-work-request-id but do not return a KnowledgeBase body.",
    "Pinned provider implementation: oci_adm_knowledge_base waits on service-sdk GetWorkRequest and ListWorkRequestErrors for create, update, delete, and compartment-change flows. The reviewed runtime keeps using service-sdk GetWorkRequest polling and shared async status instead of provider helper waiters.",
    "Repo-authored bind-versus-create stays explicit: when no OCI identifier is tracked, the runtime uses paginated ListKnowledgeBases matches on exact compartmentId plus displayName and optional tracked knowledgeBaseId/id, ignores DELETING, DELETED, and FAILED summaries, and fails on duplicate exact-name matches instead of adopting arbitrarily.",
    "Repo-authored mutation policy stays explicit: only displayName, freeformTags, and definedTags reconcile in place. The provider's ChangeKnowledgeBaseCompartment support remains out-of-scope drift because the published runtime treats compartmentId as replacement-only and never calls ChangeKnowledgeBaseCompartment."
